   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>10.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Some of the People of Israel</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Rising Early in the Morning That They May Run</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>after Liquor and Lingering into the Evening</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>That Wine May Inflame Them</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Some of the people of Israel rose early in the morning that they might run after liquor and lingered into the evening that wine might inflame them.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>They amused themselves with lyre, lute, tambourine, flute, and wine in their banquets, not considering what had been done by Jehovah nor regarding the work of His hands 5:11-12 .</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>We should consider ourselves in the light of this word.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>How do we behave ourselves in the morning and in the evening?</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>11.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Some among the People of Israel</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Drawing Iniquity with Ropes</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>of Vanity and Sin as with Cart Ropes</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Some among the people of Israel drew iniquity with ropes of vanity and sin as with cart ropes 5:18 .</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>They went so far as to ridicule Jehovah by saying, "He should hurry up;/He should hasten His work,/So that we may see it;/And the counsel of the Holy One of Israel/Should draw near and happen,/So that we may know it!" v. 19 . These evil, insulting words indicate that these people did not have any fear of God.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>They did not even believe in God; they had become atheists.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>12.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Some of the People of Israel</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Calling Good Evil, and Evil Good</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Some of the people of Israel called good evil, and evil good 5:20 .</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>They made darkness light, and light darkness.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>They also made bitterness sweetness, and sweetness bitterness.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>They turned everything upside down.</S>
   </TEXT>
